<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Always refer to your pet by its proper name.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Gobaner</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> may only be around a short while <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>this time</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, but he is certain to return.  You don't want to camp a spawn for ten hours with a pet who is holding an old grudge.  Whenever I post stories to the web about my adventures, I always give my pet's proper name.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Give your copper pieces to your pet:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> I have found I get better service generally by tipping.  Don't drop excess coinage, give it to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Xibeker</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  I have a much easier time with pet control now that I have a reputation as a generous summoner.  In a similar vein, give your pet any loot which will not be carried out, for example, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ancient Coins, Bloodgill Goblin Skin, Severed Heads</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and so on.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Equip your pet!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I know, at 52nd level, it's not supposed to make a difference, but a pet with weapons <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> looks cooler</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and all of us like to look cool.  Sometimes I buy those wicked looking <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Kunark</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> weapons just to hand to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Vbtik</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  And when the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>other</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> pets see how you are treating <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>yours</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->, they will be eager to be summoned.  Weapons with a <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> proc</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> of course are especially fine.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Armor your pet!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> This does have a definite game benefit.  You can summon about a dozen AC in rings and stones, but also give <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Lonann</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>every piece of rawhide and ringmail that drops</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->.  You were just going to throw it away anyway.  Also all those NO DROP LORE pieces of armor for some quest you have no idea about.  If I know I have a long camp, I sometimes buy leather tunic for it.  Armoring your pet lets it know that it is appreciated!<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Buff your pet!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> They love it as much as warriors do, and for the same reasons.  Shapersons <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> (as we call them here in California)</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> make excellent hunting partners for this very reason.  Even rangers and paladins can make a big difference.  Make <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Venn</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>part of the team!</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Always wave good bye to your pet before dispersing him, gating, or zoning.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  It takes just a few seconds to target <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Geker</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> and <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> /bye</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->, and it lets him know you appreciate it.  I do this even if I am just resummoning to get a blue pet.  Remember, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Geker</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is off levelling somewhere, and may return to you more powerful than ever.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Treat your group leader as <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>your</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> Master!</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  Whenever I receive a command from my group or raid leader, I <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> always</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> acknowledge it with an appropriate message.  For example, when <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>auto-following</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> I say <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> 'Elendel is my leader, following Elendel!'</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  This lets <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Lobarer</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> know that you are not asking anything of it that is not expected of yourself.<br>
<br>
Just keep in mind these handy hints, and I am sure you will find your pets are higher level, better behaved, and last longer.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Razamatazz Pizzazz</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
Senior Elementalist<br>
Ancient Fellowship<br>
Xev<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showPrevMessage?topicID=29.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showNextMessage?topicID=29.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=29.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.threadControl?topicID=29.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/unread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=29.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowergoofystuff.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=29.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub102.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="themagicianstowerannouncements">Administration<option value="themagicianstowergeneral">General<option value="themagicianstowerfrm32">Class Balance<option value="themagicianstowerfrm45">User Interface<option value="themagicianstowerspells">Spells<option value="themagicianstowerequipmentandquests">Quests<option value="themagicianstowerfrm28">Equipment<option value="themagicianstowerfrm29">Magician Pets<option value="themagicianstowe